Description: ABS Provides innovative software solutions for distributors and retailers .
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: In the early 1970s, most distributors had some type of system to handle accounting, such as Accounts Receivable, but inventory control was virtually always done manually on cardboard stock record cards stored on a "Lazy Susan" in the middle of the order entry / customer service area. Two notable exceptions were J.J. Haines in Baltimore, MD and Empire Carpet  in Teterboro, NJ. These companies wanted to computerize more aspects of their business, including inventory control, and move to a bigger computer system capable of handling more on-line users. At the time, this was considered "leading edge", since there were very few ways to do this, short of purchasing a "mainframe" computer costing millions of dollars to buy, and many more hundreds of thousands of dollars to maintain each year.Their Smart Warehouse software has given their customers a 21st Century Showroom. Using a smart phone, our customers can scan products in their showroom, check pricing and availability, and even produce a quote for their customer. The information can be printed locally on a network printer or e-mailed directly to their customer.

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Investment banking firm Cresta Capital is led by an accomplished and proven team of financial professionals. Cresta Capital’s investment team has executed hundreds of transactions, some ranging as high as $150 million. Cresta Capital’s management members, who possess an average of 20 years of experience in the industry, employ their expertise in advising businesses of all sizes in the areas of mergers and acquisitions, capital raising, market assessment, competitive analyses, and business model creation. Cresta Capital’s management team includes Chairman of the Board Avi Mirman, President and Chief Compliance Officer Michael Mirman, and Managing Director Russell Steward, CFA. Avi Mirman has served as Cresta Capital’s Chairman since 2006. Prior to joining Cresta Capital, Avi Mirman founded Maximum Ventures, Inc., an investment banking consultancy that specialized in providing services to smaller capitalization companies. Before taking the reins at Cresta Capital, Avi Mirman led his office at GunnAllen Financial to become one of the highest ranked offices in the company in regards to gross production and capital monies raised. Cresta Capital hired Michael Mirman as President in June of 2006 and added the additional position of Chief Compliance Officer in January of 2010. A 15-year veteran of the securities industry, Michael Mirman came to Cresta Capital from an investment arm of GunnAllen Financial, where he raised over $150 million. Michael Mirman also possesses investment banking experience from his time with Maximum Ventures, Inc. and Citicorp Investment Services. Cresta Capital’s Managing Director, Russell Steward, CFA, possesses more than 15 years of experience in investment banking and private equity dealings, which he now applies to building Cresta Capital’s client base. Before joining Cresta Capital in 2010, Russell Steward headed operations at a number of successful firms, including SMH Capital Advisors, Inc., G.C. Andersen Partners, LLC, BT Alex. Brown, and PaineWebber Group Inc.

Description: Finite Element Analysis simulation
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: NEi Software provides analysis, simulation, and virtual test software used by mechanical engineers to virtually determine the stress, deformation, dynamics, vibration modes, fatigue, kinematics, fluid dynamics, heat transfer, and other performance parameters of product designs.   The software uses 3D digital prototypes, typically imported from 3D CAD software, and applies structural or thermal loads and boundary conditions. The software provides results in the form of data, plots, and 3D graphic visualizations, and animations that show engineers how parts and assemblies will perform.  NEi Software saves companies time and money, promotes quality and encourages innovation by improving the design process.   Engineers can more easily explore design alternatives, optimize parts, reduce the number of physical prototypes, catch problem areas, eliminate numerous redesigns, and develop more appropriate test programs. The main product NEi Nastran is an industry proven Finite Element Analysis solver that works with all major industry pre and post processors including Femap by Siemens PLM Software and in-house brands NEi Fusion and NEi Works for SolidWorks. NEi Nastran is used worldwide in aerospace, automotive, maritime, petroleum, medical, sports and consumer products. The website provides video demos, webinars, White Papers, and tutorials on FEA and engineering simulation topics.

Description: StormBlok Systems, Inc. was formed in 1999 to address Hurricane damage to manufactured homes. The concept was simple: use the wind instead
Full Description: StormBlok Systems, Inc. was formed in 1999 to address Hurricane damage to manufactured homes. The concept was simple: use the wind instead of fight it like all other products on the market place. As the Product developed and testing was initiated it became clear that the concept of using the wind had far greater applications. StormBlok finalized testing of the hurricane protection system for homes in 2005 and also started developing new technology for commercial signs, ATM machines, gas station pumps and windows. All of the new technology was based around the reduction of wind loads through the use of Pyramid technology. They realized that by placing a pyramid over a protected object you would reduce surface area, reduce the angle of attack and create an impact barrier out and away from what was being tested.

Description: Riverford Exploration, LLC is an Oil & Gas Exploration and Production Company and Oil & Gas Consulting Business.
Full Description: Riverford Exploration, LLC is an Oil & Gas Exploration and Production Company and Oil & Gas Consulting Business with offices in The Woodlands and Dallas, Texas. Riverford Exploration, LLC was founded in 2003 and has producing oil & gas assets in Elm Coulee, Bakken Field, Montana; Oklahoma Scoop; and Permian, Midland and Delaware Basins.  Riverford's Co-Founder, Bill Fairhurst, has been involved in the majority of U.S. resource plays prior to the resource revolution.  Bill is credited with placing his company in Elm Coulee, Bakken Field prior to its discovery.  Elm Coulee Field is the largest onshore U.S. discovery in 56 years.  Bill is also credited with economic discovery of the WolfBone play in the Delaware Basin.   The WolfBone discovery brought Reeves County, Texas production from less than 3,000 BOPD to over 100,000 BOPD in less than five years and is the primary resource play being exploited by major and Independent Oil & Gas companies in the Southern Delaware Basin.  He and his innovative teams have also discovered dozens of new fields in traditional plays throughout the United States.

Full Description: DexType is a program that allows you to use a gesture recognition device to control Chrome. DexType is the world's first truly "virtual" keyboard.  You can use DexType with a gesture recognition device like the LEAP to control your browser without needing a keyboard or a mouse.  The keyboard uses a disambiguation algorithm to allow you to type coherently without needing to be overly precise with your keystrokes, but also allows for definitive keystrokes when needed.  DexType is incredibly easy to learn, and includes a tool set that gives you all the options and functionality you need to navigate the web without having to touch anything at all.  DexType includes dictionaries for 26 languages, with more to come soon.
